# Enroute Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## 1. Introduction
This PRD defines the functional and non-functional requirements for Enroute, an AI-powered career navigation platform, and its accompanying Admin/Mentor Web Portal. It serves as the master guide for feature development.

## 2. Goals & Objectives
- **Primary Goal**: Reduce career decision paralysis by providing a unified, personalized journey planner and AI mentorship.
- **Secondary Goal**: Provide Career Counselors and Mentors a dashboard to track, guide, and analyze student/user progress efficiently.

## 3. User Stories

### As a Student / App User, I want to...
- Take a Personalized Career Test to discover potential paths and institutions.
- Interact with Dahlia (AI) via Voice or Text to ask career questions and record voice ideas.
- Scan my existing CV to identify skill gaps and generate improvements.
- Receive a tailored step-by-step roadmap for my desired role (e.g., "Software Engineer") with estimated timelines, required diplomas, and salary data.
- Search for specific Universities, Institutions, or Mentors using smart AI search and filters.
- Connect with human Mentors listed in the service directory for direct guidance.
- Receive announcements for events, forums, competitions, and scholarships, along with deadline notifications.

### As a Career Counselor / Mentor (Web Portal Admin), I want to...
- View anonymized analytics on student skill gaps, roadmap completions, and engagement.
- Manage my Mentor Profile so students can find my services.
- Post announcements (events, scholarships) directly to the mobile app.
- Monitor the success rate of career placements to adjust institutional guidance.

## 4. Functional Requirements

| Category | Feature | Description | Priority |
|----------|---------|-------------|----------|
| **Core AI** | Dahlia Interaction | Real-time voice/text chat, recording, transcription, AI guidance | P0 |
| **Model** | Custom Dahlia AI | Dedicated fine-tuned LLM or RAG pipeline specifically trained on Philippine career paths and empathetic counseling | P0 |
| **Discovery**| Personalized Career Test | Gamified onboarding/testing yielding tailored field/university recs | P0 |
| **Planning** | Career Roadmaps | AI-generated step-by-step learning paths + CV Analysis | P0 |
| **Search** | Smart DB Search | Searchable directories for Institutions, Careers, and Mentors | P1 |
| **Network** | Mentor System | Directory of mentors with profiles, allowing users to connect | P1 |
| **Updates** | Announcements | Feed for events, scholarships, and deadline push notifications | P2 |
| **Admin** | Web Dashboard | React web app for analytics, mentor management, announcement posting | P1 |

## 5. Non-Functional Requirements
- **Performance**: Mobile app must load swiftly; voice interactions require < 3s latency.
- **UX/UI**: Sleek dark-mode interface with vibrant accents. The design MUST feel premium, modern, and engaging.
- **Data Governance**: Secure handling of CVs, voice data, and personal profiles via rigorous Firebase Auth & security rules.

## 6. Out of Scope (MVP)
- Deep video conferencing integration within the app (mentor contacts will use external links initially).
- Complex payment gateways.

> **Note**: This PRD must be referenced when evaluating feature completeness during vibe-coding sessions.